allTests: function()

It starts all tests which this class contains.  Info about whether test passed or not is written in console.  Console is in google chrome and in firebug extension for Firefox.

testSolvePlainDBA1

testSolvePlainDBA1: function()

It tests solvePlainDBA function of Tree.  Function gets array of elements consisting of two attributes and boolean and.  Correct answer is one DBA containing these two.

testSolvePlainDBA2

testSolvePlainDBA2: function()

testSolvePlainDBA3

testSolvePlainDBA3: function()

testSolvePlainDBA4

testSolvePlainDBA4: function()

It tests solvePlainDBA function of Tree.  Function gets array of elements consisting of three attributes and two booleans (and).  Array contains also some other elements which are unimportant.  I am testing different start and end than beginning and end of the array.

testSolvePlainDBA5

testSolvePlainDBA5: function()

It tests solvePlainDBA function of Tree.  Function gets array of elements consisting of only one attributes in brackets.

testSolveRule

testSolveRule: function()

It tests solveRule function of Tree.  Function gets array of elements consisting of only attributes and booleans(and, or) It tests if it can correctly pass data to function solvePlainDBA and give correct answer.

testSolveRule1

testSolveRule1: function()

It tests solveRule function of Tree.  Function gets array of elements consisting of attributes, booleans(and, or) and It tests if it can correctly pass data to function solvePlainDBA and give correct answer.

testSolveRule2

testSolveRule2: function()

It tests solveRule function of Tree.  Function gets array of elements consisting of attributes, booleans(and, or) and It tests if negation is correctly solved

testSolveRule3

testSolveRule3: function()

It tests solveRule function of Tree.  Function gets array of elements consisting of attributes, booleans(and, or) and It tests if negation conibed with brackets is correctly solved
